The article is a joint statement from the Presidents of France, the Russian Federation, and the United States of America, who are the co-chairs of the OSCE Minsk Group. They express their commitment to a peaceful resolution of the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict and urge the leaders of Armenia and Azerbaijan to make important decisions to reach a lasting settlement. They call for the fulfillment of the commitment made in a joint statement in January 2012 and emphasize the need to refrain from maximalist positions, respect the ceasefire agreement, and avoid hostile rhetoric. The article stresses that military force will not resolve the conflict and urges the parties to seek a peaceful, negotiated settlement. The co-chair countries pledge to continue working closely with the sides and encourage the use of the assistance of the Minsk Group Co-Chairs as mediators. Ultimately, they believe that peace will depend on the parties' willingness to seek an agreement based on mutual understanding and a shared vision of the benefits of peace.